          }
        },
        "text_LHGLnM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>A heel spur is an abnormal growth of the heel bone caused by calcium deposits. Calcium deposits form when the plantar fascia pulls away from the heel, leading to a bony protrusion known as a heel spur. <br/><br/>Heel spurs can cause severe pain in the rearfoot, especially while standing or walking. Women have a higher incidence of heel spurs, partly due to the types of footwear they commonly wear.</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.6,
